1
00:00:01,110 --> 00:00:03,480
(Episode 117)

2
00:00:07,610 --> 00:00:08,610
What's this?

3
00:00:08,680 --> 00:00:12,650
When I met Chairman Ma 30 years ago,
while pregnant with Dong Seok's child,

4
00:00:12,920 --> 00:00:15,350
Chairman Ma gave it to me.
You remember, right?

5
00:00:15,350 --> 00:00:16,450
Yes.

6
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:18,190
Of course. I remember.

7
00:00:18,190 --> 00:00:19,920
Here's the key. Go on, open it.

8
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:33,810
This is...

9
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:38,240
By the way, something has been
bothering me for a long time.

10
00:00:38,710 --> 00:00:43,080
When Father gave this to me,
there were two golden toads, right?

11
00:00:44,020 --> 00:00:47,350
But back then, when I moved
into the Chairman's house with Seo Rin,

12
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:48,750
I didn't get a chance
to grab this until later.

13
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:53,830
I was so busy with Seo Rin and Chairman Ma
that I didn't check it until later.

14
00:00:54,490 --> 00:00:57,130
But one of the golden toads was missing,
and I couldn't find it anywhere.

15
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:07,970
Really?

16
00:01:08,940 --> 00:01:12,240
All I did was bring you
this jewelry box as you asked.

17
00:01:12,710 --> 00:01:14,780
Do you think that housekeeper
we had back then...

18
00:01:15,610 --> 00:01:17,050
could have stolen it?

19
00:01:18,150 --> 00:01:19,150
It's hard to say.

20
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:23,350
Anyway, it's been so long,
it'd be impossible to find her now.

21
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:26,090
And even if we did,
she would've sold it by now.

22
00:01:27,290 --> 00:01:28,790
Just make sure you keep this one safe.

23
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:31,460
Yes, I will.

24
00:01:38,340 --> 00:01:40,940
But one of the golden toads was missing,
and I couldn't find it anywhere.

25
00:01:41,510 --> 00:01:44,980
Why would she bring that up now?
She's making me anxious.

26
00:01:45,510 --> 00:01:46,640
What are you so anxious about?

27
00:01:47,450 --> 00:01:49,380
You're here.

28
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:52,920
You seem to talk to yourself a lot,
Manager Lee.

29
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:55,090
Yes. Please, excuse me.

30
00:01:57,460 --> 00:01:58,760
I've been meaning to talk to you.

31
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,100
What's your relationship with my mother?

32
00:02:07,630 --> 00:02:09,830
- There's nothing between us.
- Nothing between you?

33
00:02:10,540 --> 00:02:14,410
Then why do my parents keep bringing up
your name, Manager Lee?

34
00:02:15,610 --> 00:02:19,380
It's true that Professor Kang and I
don't get along.

35
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:23,950
As for Lawyer Han,
we help each other out professionally,

36
00:02:24,350 --> 00:02:26,450
but we're cordial, that's all.

37
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:28,650
It's nothing more than that,
so please don't get the wrong idea.

38
00:02:28,950 --> 00:02:29,950
Hold on a second.

39
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:33,530
I have a question for you
as a lawyer for the Legal Team.

40
00:02:37,660 --> 00:02:41,230
What time did you go to the hospital
after hearing about Seo Rin's death?

41
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:45,000
You can find all that information
in my police statement.

42
00:02:45,740 --> 00:02:46,800
Regardless,

43
00:02:47,540 --> 00:02:49,070
did you and CEO Chae...

44
00:02:49,510 --> 00:02:52,780
head out together as soon as you heard
about Seo Rin's death?

45
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,050
Yes.

46
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:57,480
- I'm CEO Chae's assistant.
- That's strange.

47
00:02:58,780 --> 00:03:01,150
CEO Chae was at a spa on that day.

48
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:04,060
Did you follow her all the way there?

49
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:07,830
Did you wait for CEO Chae
until she was done?

50
00:03:08,790 --> 00:03:11,460
My understanding is that...

51
00:03:11,830 --> 00:03:14,500
you rarely accompany her
on her personal schedule.

52
00:03:14,830 --> 00:03:16,470
Well...

53
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:22,210
She got a call about Director Ma's case,
and then she called me.

54
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:25,140
As a lawyer for the Legal Team
investigating this case,

55
00:03:25,610 --> 00:03:28,050
I requested the phone records
from the carrier.

56
00:03:28,650 --> 00:03:29,710
But that's funny.

57
00:03:29,950 --> 00:03:32,750
The tower for CEO Chae's calls that day...

58
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:36,750
and the records of your incoming calls
don't match up at all.

59
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:39,220
That's...

60
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:43,230
I must have misremembered.

61
00:03:44,130 --> 00:03:45,130
That day,

62
00:03:45,930 --> 00:03:48,130
I went to pick up CEO Chae
around the time...

63
00:03:48,130 --> 00:03:49,370
her spa appointment was finishing,

64
00:03:50,270 --> 00:03:53,270
and she answered a call saying
something had happened to Director Ma.

65
00:03:53,740 --> 00:03:57,440
So I rushed CEO Chae to the hospital
where the incident occurred.

66
00:03:57,980 --> 00:03:59,610
Is that so?

67
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:02,750
I see.

68
00:04:15,290 --> 00:04:17,330
That's...

69
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:20,970
I must have misremembered.

70
00:04:21,370 --> 00:04:22,400
That day,

71
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:24,470
I went to pick up CEO Chae
around the time...

72
00:04:24,470 --> 00:04:25,870
her spa appointment was finishing,

73
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:29,170
and she answered a call saying
something had happened to Director Ma.

74
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:33,340
So I rushed CEO Chae to the hospital
where the incident occurred.

75
00:04:33,410 --> 00:04:36,480
Baek Ho, were you really able
to get the phone records?

76
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:38,820
No. Even as a lawyer,

77
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,990
I can't access CEO Chae's call history.

78
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:43,350
So he fell for your bluff.

79
00:04:43,490 --> 00:04:47,530
Yes. But unfortunately,
we can't use this as evidence.

80
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:51,030
They could claim I used deceptive tactics.

81
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:55,170
However, this does suggest that
CEO Chae and Manager Lee...

82
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:58,200
are using a burner phone
that can't be traced.

83
00:04:58,770 --> 00:05:03,010
And it also shatters CEO Chae's alibi
about being at the spa.

84
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:04,180
Chae Hwa Young.

85
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:08,450
The evidence that she killed Seo Rin
is finally starting to surface.

86
00:05:08,910 --> 00:05:11,450
It feels like the puzzle pieces
are finally falling into place.

87
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:14,290
Here.

88
00:05:20,590 --> 00:05:23,190
I've never seen you this stressed, ma'am.

89
00:05:24,430 --> 00:05:26,300
Today, no matter what it takes,

90
00:05:26,530 --> 00:05:29,970
I'm going to make sure Chairman Ali sees
our investment proposal.

91
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,400
But wouldn't it be dangerous...

92
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:35,410
if Chairman Ma or Oh Jang Mi finds out
about our plan?

93
00:05:35,770 --> 00:05:36,770
They won't find out.

94
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:39,640
Ali isn't here to invest
in Dream Hotel specifically.

95
00:05:39,980 --> 00:05:42,110
She is here looking for opportunities.

96
00:05:57,660 --> 00:06:00,770
I wonder what Chairman Ali even
looks like.

97
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:03,940
Doesn't she get hot under all that?

98
00:06:04,070 --> 00:06:05,940
It's so annoying just looking at her.

99
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:10,980
But I'm sure I've seen those eyes
somewhere before.

100
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:12,880
Why do they look so familiar?

101
00:06:13,810 --> 00:06:14,810
What?

102
00:06:15,210 --> 00:06:16,650
Chairman.

103
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:20,380
Are you enjoying the service
I recommended?

104
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:23,020
Okay. I'm pleased.

105
00:06:23,420 --> 00:06:26,120
The artist here is very talented.

106
00:06:26,990 --> 00:06:28,930
Thank you, Chairman.

107
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:31,130
I've never seen you this pleased before.

108
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:34,270
Alright, it's time to make my move.

109
00:06:34,530 --> 00:06:35,870
Okay, thank you.

110
00:06:36,470 --> 00:06:39,300
I'll be the star
of the embassy party tomorrow.

111
00:06:40,610 --> 00:06:43,070
Chairman, there's something
I'd like to discuss.

112
00:06:44,140 --> 00:06:45,280
Okay, go ahead.

113
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:50,850
As the CEO of this hotel,

114
00:06:51,350 --> 00:06:53,380
I'd like to talk business.

115
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,290
There you go lying again.

116
00:06:55,350 --> 00:06:57,660
You're just an employee, not the CEO.

117
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:02,390
Go to the bathroom and turn on the faucet.

118
00:07:17,010 --> 00:07:20,310
Jang Mi, bring Kang Jun Ho
to the lobby right now.

119
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:24,820
I'll make sure her own son sees her
groveling at my feet.

120
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:28,620
I'm going to make her feel
the depths of humiliation today.

121
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:31,290
Okay, Mom. I'll be rooting for you.

122
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:33,120
What did your mom say?

123
00:07:33,460 --> 00:07:35,030
Where's General Manager Kang right now?

124
00:07:43,770 --> 00:07:47,470
- Chairman, the restaurant is this way.
- What's with you?

125
00:07:47,470 --> 00:07:48,470
Excuse me?

126
00:07:48,910 --> 00:07:49,940
What's wrong?

127
00:07:50,210 --> 00:07:51,580
Take your shoes off.

128
00:07:51,580 --> 00:07:54,280
What? What's the issue here?

129
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:56,950
You're making a huge mistake.

130
00:07:58,180 --> 00:07:59,680
- Pardon?
- Mrs. Chae.

131
00:08:00,180 --> 00:08:01,950
Take off those leather shoes, now.

132
00:08:03,290 --> 00:08:04,360
But...

133
00:08:04,990 --> 00:08:07,190
Why do you want me to take these off?

134
00:08:07,260 --> 00:08:09,260
Don't you know our Chairman's origins?

135
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:13,260
- You're wearing leather shoes.
- Right.

136
00:08:14,130 --> 00:08:15,870
Chairman, I am so sorry.

137
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:20,440
It completely slipped my mind.
I'll be more careful.

138
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:24,780
But in my country, we wear leather shoes.

139
00:08:29,580 --> 00:08:31,950
Your hospitality gets a zero.

140
00:08:32,350 --> 00:08:35,150
You've disrespected
my country's traditions.

141
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:38,190
I'm so sorry.
If I beg for your forgiveness like this...

142
00:08:38,260 --> 00:08:41,160
No. Bow to the shoes and confess your sin.

143
00:08:41,890 --> 00:08:42,890
What?

144
00:08:43,430 --> 00:08:45,130
Isn't that taking it a bit too far?

145
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,730
I can't stay in this hotel.
Let's go to another one.

146
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,770
No, please. I'm sorry.

147
00:08:50,230 --> 00:08:52,400
Chairman, I'll do it.
I'll beg for your forgiveness.

148
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:06,020
Beg for my forgiveness like you mean it.

149
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:09,620
This is not the attitude of someone
who wants an investment.

150
00:09:09,890 --> 00:09:10,890
Yes, I understand.

151
00:09:13,590 --> 00:09:15,160
I have committed a grave sin.

152
00:09:16,530 --> 00:09:17,660
Please forgive me.

153
00:09:21,270 --> 00:09:22,300
Hey, Tommy.

154
00:09:22,870 --> 00:09:26,770
Mrs. Chae.
Kiss the shoes and sincerely apologize.

155
00:09:27,070 --> 00:09:28,070
What did you say?

156
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:30,370
How could you ask me to do such a thing?

157
00:09:30,370 --> 00:09:32,380
It's the only way to appease her.

158
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:35,780
Otherwise, we're leaving.
And the deal is off.

159
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:53,930
I have committed a mortal sin.

160
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:55,970
Please forgive me.

161
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:12,350
Beg for forgiveness like you mean it!

162
00:10:21,630 --> 00:10:22,990
I have done something unforgivable.

163
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:24,830
Please forgive me.

164
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,500
Chae Hwa Young.
This is just the beginning.

165
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,770
You're going to suffer
much more than this.

166
00:10:58,760 --> 00:10:59,760
Chae Hwa Young.

167
00:11:00,430 --> 00:11:03,230
This humiliation in front of your son...

168
00:11:03,470 --> 00:11:06,170
is nothing compared
to the pain I've endured.

169
00:11:07,170 --> 00:11:11,580
The price for a mother's tears of blood
who has lost her child...

170
00:11:12,180 --> 00:11:14,250
is something you're about
to experience for yourself.

171
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:19,480
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

172
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:24,260
Is that woman out of her mind?

173
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:26,360
How could she order her to do that?

174
00:11:27,390 --> 00:11:28,590
And CEO Chae...

175
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:31,530
Does she really have to stoop
to that level of humiliation?

176
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:33,460
Unbelievable.

177
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,000
General Manager Kang.

178
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:42,510
You seem upset. I'll come back later.

179
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:45,380
It's fine. What is it?

180
00:11:50,850 --> 00:11:53,280
CEO Chae is quite the veteran, isn't she?

181
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:56,850
It's not easy to cater
to a VVIP's every whim.

182
00:11:57,620 --> 00:12:01,160
I guess her 30 years of experience
in this business show.

183
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:02,230
Ma Seo Rin,

184
00:12:02,930 --> 00:12:04,160
are you being sarcastic?

185
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:07,300
- It sounds like mockery to me.
- My name is Oh Jang Mi.

186
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,940
Aren't you the one mocking and toying
with me, Jun Ho?

187
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:15,540
Calling me Seo Rin is an insult to her
and shows your obsession with me.

188
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:17,240
So what's your point?

189
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:19,610
Watching what CEO Chae did today,

190
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:22,050
I was wondering
if it made you feel anything.

191
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:25,920
- What?
- Your mother being mocked...

192
00:12:26,380 --> 00:12:28,090
and humiliated in front of everybody...

193
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:31,690
is what my mother goes through
every single day.

194
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:33,620
All thanks to CEO Chae, of course.

195
00:12:34,590 --> 00:12:35,590
Compared to what my mom goes through,

196
00:12:36,060 --> 00:12:37,600
what CEO Chae is going through
is a drop in the bucket.

197
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:40,400
Are you seriously trying
to compare the two?

198
00:12:41,230 --> 00:12:44,070
I know what CEO Chae did to your mother
was wrong.

199
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:45,840
Wrong? It was the worst thing
she could do.

200
00:12:46,540 --> 00:12:49,840
Is there a worse sin than taking a child
from its mother?

201
00:12:49,940 --> 00:12:51,710
But why are you bringing this up now?

202
00:12:52,410 --> 00:12:54,080
Are you just trying
to add fuel to the fire?

203
00:12:54,150 --> 00:12:55,450
Because it reminded me of my mother.

204
00:12:56,510 --> 00:13:00,550
The humiliation she felt going outside
with everyone staring at her.

205
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:02,990
My mother goes through that
every single day.

206
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:06,420
So, since people like my mom
are out there,

207
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:09,760
don't get all heartbroken over this,
General Manager Kang.

208
00:13:11,030 --> 00:13:13,600
That's enough. Please leave.
I'd like to be alone.

209
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:17,500
I still wish you weren't
Chae Hwa Young's son...

210
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,240
but the son of Lawyer Han...

211
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:22,470
and to be Baek Ho's brother again.

212
00:13:40,690 --> 00:13:42,330
No, this can't be happening.

213
00:13:43,530 --> 00:13:45,530
What is this?
How could I be humiliated like this?

214
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:48,170
That hurts. Darn it.

215
00:13:56,710 --> 00:13:58,780
Chairman Ali said she's ready
to hear your investment pitch.

216
00:14:02,310 --> 00:14:05,880
Jang Mi, I'm heading
to Kang Jun Ho's office. Get ready.

217
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:08,750
Okay. Let's go, Tommy.

218
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:28,870
What's wrong?
Did I do something to offend you again?

219
00:14:29,510 --> 00:14:33,110
She wants to know why you called her
for business when you weren't prepared.

220
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:34,550
Chairman Ali,

221
00:14:35,150 --> 00:14:38,820
I understand you're in Korea
looking for investment opportunities.

222
00:14:39,250 --> 00:14:42,290
General Manager Kang has
a perfect proposal...

223
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:43,990
that will be right up your alley.

224
00:14:44,890 --> 00:14:46,090
Here is the investment proposal.

225
00:14:46,660 --> 00:14:47,660
Please take a look.

226
00:14:48,690 --> 00:14:50,660
General Manager Kang. What?

227
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,260
You want me to pour my money...

228
00:14:53,430 --> 00:14:55,030
into this pathetic little hotel?

229
00:14:56,870 --> 00:14:57,870
Let's go, Tommy.

230
00:14:59,070 --> 00:15:00,600
There's no need to be so hasty.

231
00:15:00,870 --> 00:15:03,840
At least hear him out, Chairman.

232
00:15:04,210 --> 00:15:06,980
Do you have any idea
what Chairman Ali is worth?

233
00:15:08,310 --> 00:15:11,320
Obviously not, or they wouldn't be
making such a pathetic proposal.

234
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:13,780
I could buy dozens,

235
00:15:13,850 --> 00:15:16,620
even hundreds of low-class hotels
like this in cash.

236
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:20,090
That's exactly why you should
hear our General Manager Kang out.

237
00:15:20,490 --> 00:15:22,590
We're not asking you to invest here.

238
00:15:22,730 --> 00:15:25,030
We propose acquiring the Hills Hotel.

239
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:27,400
We can absolutely guarantee...

240
00:15:27,670 --> 00:15:29,670
the huge return on investment
you're looking for.

241
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:31,000
Isn't that right, General Manager Kang?

242
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:32,440
Go on, tell her.

243
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:34,310
Forget it.

244
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,680
If you're not interested,
we'll find another investor.

245
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:39,810
If you're not interested,
there's the door.

246
00:15:39,810 --> 00:15:41,580
General Manager Kang,
have you lost your mind?

247
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:52,220
General Manager Kang,
you've got some nerve.

248
00:15:52,990 --> 00:15:57,360
All this confidence
is actually piquing my interest.

249
00:15:57,660 --> 00:15:59,030
Okay, let's hear it.

250
00:16:02,870 --> 00:16:05,000
Go on, General Manager Kang.
Give her the briefing.

251
00:16:08,710 --> 00:16:11,010
Our vision for acquiring the Hills Hotel
is flawless.

252
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:15,150
By combining your immense capital
with our hotel's infrastructure,

253
00:16:15,550 --> 00:16:17,880
we can create
a mega-hotel that will dominate...

254
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:18,980
the Asian market overnight.

255
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:20,850
Your vision?

256
00:16:22,350 --> 00:16:24,360
- I'm not so sure.
- Excuse me?

257
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:27,760
Is there something you are not satisfied
with now?

258
00:16:27,990 --> 00:16:31,060
The Chairman won't invest in any company
with leadership risk.

259
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:33,960
Not even one dollar.

260
00:16:34,530 --> 00:16:38,400
You faced criminal charges in the past,
didn't you?

261
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:42,070
You're a CEO who's already been
taken down once.

262
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:45,340
If I lose money because of
the controversy surrounding you,

263
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:47,110
then what?

264
00:16:47,180 --> 00:16:49,380
I was cleared of all charges.

265
00:16:49,710 --> 00:16:51,980
I was framed. It was a complete setup.

266
00:16:54,820 --> 00:16:55,820
Chairman Ali,

267
00:16:56,220 --> 00:16:59,360
as a fellow corporate leader,
you know very well...

268
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:03,190
a CEO isn't judged by their excuses
or their methods,

269
00:17:03,590 --> 00:17:05,600
they're judged by their numbers,
wouldn't you agree?

270
00:17:06,530 --> 00:17:09,770
Kang Jun Ho is unusually composed.

271
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,800
What's making him be that bold
to turn the tables...

272
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:13,440
when questioned about leadership risk?

273
00:17:14,410 --> 00:17:16,110
That means he's got an ace up his sleeve.

274
00:17:16,540 --> 00:17:17,910
Could it be the power of
his massive slush fund?

275
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:21,250
But if you're willing to take a chance
and bet on our vision,

276
00:17:21,650 --> 00:17:23,350
I'll deliver an ROI so overwhelming...

277
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:25,880
that you'll forget your concern about
leadership-related risk.

278
00:17:29,690 --> 00:17:30,690
Wait a minute.

279
00:17:30,950 --> 00:17:33,990
That's right.
I'm sure I've seen those eyes...

280
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:35,530
somewhere before.

281
00:17:42,630 --> 00:17:44,300
Ma'am, I think Kang Baek Ho...

282
00:17:44,370 --> 00:17:46,870
Her voice and eyes are so familiar.

283
00:17:47,840 --> 00:17:50,240
What? What about Kang Baek Ho?

284
00:17:50,540 --> 00:17:52,940
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho is questioning
your alibi...

285
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:55,050
on the day of Seo Rin's accident.

286
00:17:55,650 --> 00:17:56,650
Let him.

287
00:17:57,280 --> 00:18:00,220
Looks like he's making a move to help
Oh Jang Mi and Jung Suk Hee.

288
00:18:02,050 --> 00:18:04,420
I swear I will rip you to shreds.

289
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:08,160
I'll rip your organs out one by one...

290
00:18:08,390 --> 00:18:12,500
and make you die in agony, Chae Hwa Young!

291
00:18:15,730 --> 00:18:18,340
Beg for forgiveness like you mean it!

292
00:18:22,510 --> 00:18:24,210
What's wrong, ma'am?

293
00:18:25,310 --> 00:18:27,040
I think Chairman Ali is Jung Suk Hee.

294
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:29,450
- Jung Suk Hee.
- Pardon?

295
00:18:29,910 --> 00:18:31,080
Goodness, CEO Chae.

296
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:33,680
What do you mean by that?

297
00:18:34,220 --> 00:18:37,490
I think Chairman Ali is Jung Suk Hee!
No, she is Jung Suk Hee.

298
00:18:37,990 --> 00:18:40,560
Her voice and that look in her eyes
are identical to Jung Suk Hee's.

299
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:42,130
What are you talking about?

300
00:18:42,660 --> 00:18:44,630
Jung Suk Hee hasn't even regained
her senses yet.

301
00:18:45,030 --> 00:18:46,960
How could she be posing as Chairman Ali?

302
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,830
That's ridiculous.

303
00:18:49,330 --> 00:18:50,930
You haven't seen her up close.

304
00:18:51,470 --> 00:18:54,510
The look in her eyes from behind her veil
and that mocking voice...

305
00:18:55,070 --> 00:18:56,810
I'm certain it is Jung Suk Hee.

306
00:18:58,780 --> 00:19:00,880
I'm right. It has to be Jung Suk Hee.

307
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:03,180
That's why she made me
take off my shoes...

308
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,620
and made me do that crazy stuff yesterday,

309
00:19:05,620 --> 00:19:07,350
just to humiliate me.

310
00:19:08,490 --> 00:19:10,220
I'll make Jung Suk Hee pay.

311
00:19:10,620 --> 00:19:14,320
- I'm going to tear her to shreds.
- I'll...

312
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,860
I'll go and confirm it myself.

313
00:19:17,330 --> 00:19:20,160
Right, Kang Hyuk.
Go to her side dish shop.

314
00:19:20,430 --> 00:19:21,900
If Jung Suk Hee isn't there,

315
00:19:22,870 --> 00:19:26,000
it means Ali is Jung Suk Hee.
My hunch has to be right.

316
00:19:26,140 --> 00:19:27,970
I'll call you the moment I confirm it.

317
00:19:29,610 --> 00:19:30,770
How dare she trick me?

318
00:19:31,740 --> 00:19:32,740
Jung Suk Hee.

319
00:19:33,910 --> 00:19:35,510
She must have gotten her memory back.

320
00:19:36,350 --> 00:19:38,250
This has Oh Jang Mi's fingerprints
all over it.

321
00:19:38,450 --> 00:19:40,550
Just like when she pretended to be
Ma Seo Rin and came for my throat.

322
00:19:40,950 --> 00:19:42,590
This is her M.O.

323
00:19:45,460 --> 00:19:47,660
A CEO isn't judged by their excuses
or their methods.

324
00:19:48,060 --> 00:19:50,130
They're judged by their numbers,
wouldn't you agree?

325
00:19:50,790 --> 00:19:52,400
I'll deliver an ROI so overwhelming...

326
00:19:53,130 --> 00:19:55,230
that you'll forget your concern about
leadership-related risk.

327
00:19:56,830 --> 00:20:00,640
Baek Ho, you looked into
Chae Hwa Young's slush fund before, right?

328
00:20:01,770 --> 00:20:05,410
Jang Mi. You were right
about the hotel supply company.

329
00:20:05,410 --> 00:20:07,340
For years, they've just been
faking the bidding process.

330
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:10,380
And it turns out most of the people
involved are connected to CEO Chae.

331
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:15,120
That's right. I've looked
into how they siphoned money...

332
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:16,150
by inflating the hotel supply costs.

333
00:20:16,150 --> 00:20:17,690
About Chae Hwa Young's slush fund...

334
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:20,460
Do you know the exact amount?

335
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:21,830
No, Mom.

336
00:20:22,190 --> 00:20:25,260
But seeing how ridiculously confident
Kang Jun Ho is,

337
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:28,000
it must mean he has a massive amount
of money stashed away.

338
00:20:28,130 --> 00:20:31,070
We need to trace the flow
of that slush fund right away.

339
00:20:31,540 --> 00:20:33,500
The way he's trying to buy up
Hills Hotel means...

340
00:20:33,570 --> 00:20:35,910
the slush fund he's built up
must be massive.

341
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:44,010
Look, no one wants you here,
so get out now.

342
00:20:44,350 --> 00:20:47,580
- Where is Jung Suk Hee?
- It's none of your business where she is!

343
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:50,190
What's it to you?

344
00:20:50,450 --> 00:20:52,160
Mind your own business
and leave while I'm asking nicely.

345
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:54,220
So Hwa Young was right.

346
00:20:54,730 --> 00:20:56,060
Jung Suk Hee isn't here.

347
00:20:57,760 --> 00:20:59,960
Hey!

348
00:21:03,770 --> 00:21:05,440
Well? What did you find?

349
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:08,010
Jung Suk Hee isn't at her shop, is she?

350
00:21:08,010 --> 00:21:10,140
That's right. She's not here.

351
00:21:10,340 --> 00:21:13,310
I knew it. I told you, didn't I?

352
00:21:13,310 --> 00:21:14,510
I'm going to kill that...

353
00:21:18,420 --> 00:21:20,220
Hey, what do you think you're doing?

354
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:22,920
What dirty scheme brings you here
looking for my mom again?

355
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:26,160
Your family is the one with the scheme,
not me.

356
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:27,490
You punk!

357
00:21:30,660 --> 00:21:32,230
Open this door right now.

358
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:36,000
CEO Chae, you can't do this.
Chairman Ali is a VVIP guest.

359
00:21:36,070 --> 00:21:38,740
VVIP, my foot. Get out of my way.

360
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:43,140
Jung Suk Hee, open this door right now!

361
00:21:43,770 --> 00:21:46,810
Open this door!
I know all about your trickery, you witch!

362
00:21:48,650 --> 00:21:50,950
Jung Suk Hee! Darn it

363
00:21:53,250 --> 00:21:55,720
What's going on?
What do you think you're doing?

364
00:21:56,550 --> 00:21:58,920
Quit the act. Move!

365
00:22:00,390 --> 00:22:03,160
Jung Suk Hee! How dare you trick me?

366
00:22:04,290 --> 00:22:05,300
What?

367
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:15,870
My goodness.

368
00:22:18,810 --> 00:22:20,240
You're actually grabbing my collar?

369
00:22:21,410 --> 00:22:24,610
Hey. Do you have a death wish?

370
00:22:25,350 --> 00:22:28,520
- You little...
- Tae Pyung. I'm home with the groceries.

371
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:33,760
- Wait.
- Don't you dare hit Tae Pyung!

372
00:22:34,830 --> 00:22:38,560
I'm not scared anymore.
Bad guys don't frighten me.

373
00:22:38,630 --> 00:22:41,330
Get away! You monster!

374
00:22:49,870 --> 00:22:53,180
Ma'am,
Jung Suk Hee's at the side dish shop.

375
00:22:53,180 --> 00:22:54,180
What?

376
00:22:54,380 --> 00:22:55,410
Get out!

377
00:22:57,080 --> 00:22:59,450
- Get out.
- No, Chairman, please wait.

378
00:22:59,750 --> 00:23:00,950
Hold on!

379
00:23:02,020 --> 00:23:03,090
- CEO Chae!
- That hurt.

380
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:04,550
Kick her out!

381
00:23:06,690 --> 00:23:07,720
What do I do?

382
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:09,660
What am I going to do about this mess?

383
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:21,540
- How did it go, Mom?
- It was close, but we pulled it off.

384
00:23:23,040 --> 00:23:25,780
You did great, Mom.
That could have been a disaster.

385
00:23:26,110 --> 00:23:27,110
Yes.

386
00:23:29,010 --> 00:23:30,150
Thanks, Tommy.

387
00:23:30,150 --> 00:23:31,750
I appreciate you going to
all that trouble to find a stand-in.

388
00:23:31,980 --> 00:23:33,450
I'll make sure you get a nice big bonus.

389
00:23:34,450 --> 00:23:36,020
Did Chae Hwa Young fall for it?

390
00:23:36,020 --> 00:23:38,490
Yes. She's probably
having a meltdown right now.

391
00:23:39,660 --> 00:23:40,790
That's a relief.

392
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,630
That was our biggest crisis yet.

393
00:23:43,790 --> 00:23:47,160
We made it through thanks to you, Jang Mi.
You did great.

394
00:23:47,730 --> 00:23:49,700
You too, Baek Ho. You did great.

395
00:23:57,910 --> 00:23:59,940
I'm certain Ali is Jung Suk Hee.

396
00:24:00,580 --> 00:24:02,080
Manager Lee, what's taking so long?

397
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:05,980
Go to the side dish shop and confirm it
and call me right back. Got it?

398
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:10,620
Mom, Chae Hwa Young is on to you.

399
00:24:10,950 --> 00:24:12,720
She said she sent
Manager Lee to your shop.

400
00:24:12,790 --> 00:24:14,890
- Mom, where are you right now?
- What?

401
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:19,700
What should I do? I'm still in a taxi.
The traffic is especially awful today.

402
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:25,540
Tommy found the stand-in.
I'll go pick her up now.

403
00:24:25,670 --> 00:24:27,570
Mom, hurry and get to the shop.

404
00:24:28,570 --> 00:24:30,440
Baek Ho, it's in your hands.

405
00:24:31,980 --> 00:24:34,380
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

406
00:24:35,310 --> 00:24:37,410
Not so fast, Chae Hwa Young.

407
00:24:38,080 --> 00:24:39,480
I can't let you find out yet.

408
00:24:41,180 --> 00:24:42,950
That was way too close.

409
00:24:43,250 --> 00:24:44,290
Tell me about it.

410
00:24:44,790 --> 00:24:47,920
All of your mother's hard work
could have gone down the drain.

411
00:24:48,060 --> 00:24:51,630
Chae Hwa Young, that wretched woman.
How should we make her pay?

412
00:24:51,930 --> 00:24:55,670
If we don't finish her off for good,
there's no telling what she'll do next.

413
00:24:55,730 --> 00:24:58,800
Anyway, we need to drain a large amount
from her slush fund.

414
00:24:58,800 --> 00:25:00,670
It's her main weapon.

415
00:25:00,970 --> 00:25:03,140
Right. We have to pull this off.

416
00:25:08,650 --> 00:25:10,810
Do you have any idea what you made me do?

417
00:25:11,010 --> 00:25:13,680
How can you be so incompetent?

418
00:25:14,020 --> 00:25:17,090
What do I do now?
Chairman Ali will never forgive me.

419
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:18,520
What am I going to do?

420
00:25:23,130 --> 00:25:25,100
I just heard from the manager.

421
00:25:25,300 --> 00:25:27,530
What on earth did you do to Chairman Ali?

422
00:25:28,430 --> 00:25:30,200
I don't even know what came over me.

423
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:32,700
I must have lost my mind for a moment.

424
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:36,340
You blew it when it was almost in the bag.
So what are you going to do now?

425
00:25:37,210 --> 00:25:38,540
Seriously.

426
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:42,250
This is all that Jung Suk Hee's fault.

427
00:25:42,610 --> 00:25:46,850
If she hadn't shown up,
my life wouldn't have become such a mess.

428
00:25:49,390 --> 00:25:50,390
Back then,

429
00:25:51,020 --> 00:25:52,890
if only I hadn't lost Dong Seok's baby...

430
00:25:53,490 --> 00:25:55,330
I was carrying...

431
00:25:55,630 --> 00:25:56,890
The baby had...

432
00:25:57,330 --> 00:25:58,800
already passed away.

433
00:25:58,860 --> 00:26:01,360
No. That's impossible.

434
00:26:03,100 --> 00:26:06,040
Bring him back.

435
00:26:06,040 --> 00:26:07,970
I said, bring him back!

436
00:26:09,340 --> 00:26:12,540
No!

437
00:26:13,980 --> 00:26:16,580
No! Bring back my son!

438
00:26:21,250 --> 00:26:23,250
If Dong Seok's son hadn't died,

439
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:26,420
I never would have had to steal Seo Rin.

440
00:26:27,260 --> 00:26:29,060
And neither Oh Bok Gil nor Seo Rin...

441
00:26:30,030 --> 00:26:31,960
would have made me get blood on my hands.

442
00:26:35,700 --> 00:26:36,700
What if...

443
00:26:37,330 --> 00:26:38,840
What if, Hwa Young...

444
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:44,140
What if the son
you had with Ma Dong Seok...

445
00:26:46,380 --> 00:26:47,710
didn't die?

446
00:26:49,450 --> 00:26:50,950
What if he is alive somewhere?

447
00:26:57,650 --> 00:26:58,660
What?

448
00:27:00,190 --> 00:27:01,190
What?

449
00:27:02,590 --> 00:27:04,090
Are you saying my son's alive?

450
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:37,730
(The First Man)

451
00:27:37,790 --> 00:27:40,360
Let's find Baek Ho's birth parents.

452
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:42,470
This looks like a family crest.

453
00:27:42,900 --> 00:27:45,140
Looks like I have to use
Ma Seo Rin's name.

454
00:27:45,270 --> 00:27:46,870
Thank you, Chairman Ali.

455
00:27:46,970 --> 00:27:50,440
Congrats. You've walked into the grave
you dug for yourself.

456
00:27:50,870 --> 00:27:54,440
If someone has an item with this crest,
does that mean they're in your family?

457
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:58,550
- I'm looking for someone.
- A girl or a boy?

458
00:27:59,080 --> 00:28:00,220
A boy.

459
00:28:02,190 --> 00:28:04,150
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
